---
const props = Astro.props;
const { data } = props;

---

<div id="region-details" class="my-8" >
    
    <!-- Accordion Container -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
      <!-- The Political Weather -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left  bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" x="0px" y="0px" width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 64 64" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#064161]">
              <path d="M 29 7 C 25.686 7 23 9.686 23 13 L 15 13 C 11.686 13 9 15.686 9 19 L 9 45 C 9 48.314 11.686 51 15 51 L 49 51 C 52.314 51 55 48.314 55 45 L 55 19 C 55 15.686 52.314 13 49 13 L 41 13 C 41 9.686 38.314 7 35 7 L 29 7 z M 29 11 L 35 11 C 36.104 11 37 11.895 37 13 L 27 13 C 27 11.895 27.896 11 29 11 z M 15 17 L 49 17 C 50.105 17 51 17.895 51 19 L 51 27.328125 C 47.860304 27.865386 40.276945 29 32 29 C 23.725715 29 16.142076 27.866066 13 27.328125 L 13 19 C 13 17.895 13.895 17 15 17 z M 13 31.384766 C 15.851521 31.855688 20.994182 32.574326 27 32.865234 L 27 33 C 27 34.105 27.895 35 29 35 L 34 35 C 35.105 35 36 34.105 36 33 L 36 32.917969 C 42.43805 32.665598 47.988855 31.881828 51 31.384766 L 51 45 C 51 46.105 50.105 47 49 47 L 15 47 C 13.895 47 13 46.105 13 45 L 13 31.384766 z"></path>
              </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">The Political Weather</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <p>
              The 1960s in continental Europe were shaped by Cold War politics. Eastern Europe (East Germany, Czechoslovakia (Now Czechia), USSR) had strict state censorship — jazz and rock were often seen as “Western corruption,” yet young people secretly tuned into Radio Free Europe or smuggled records. In the West, France, Italy, and Germany were buzzing with post-war cultural reinvention, while the Balkans and Nordic countries balanced tradition with growing curiosity about rock, jazz, and experimental music. Student protests (especially in Paris ’68) and rising youth movements created a political backdrop that directly influenced music-making.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What People Were Hearing -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">What People Were Hearing</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <!-- Subsections -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
           <p>Before the 60s:</p> 
            Folk and regional traditions still dominated 
            — from Russian balalaika ensembles to flamenco in Spain, rebetiko in Greece, fado in Portugal, and polkas in Central Europe. Accordion, mandolin, and local strings were everyday instruments.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center space-x-2">
              <img src="https://syvkefpljdcoricvmqcy.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/images/europe_assets/content_images/Balailaka.png" alt="Russian balalaika" class="w-32 h-auto">
              <span class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Russian balalaika </span> <br/>
              </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <p>In the 60s:</p>
              <p>Western rock ’n’ roll filtered in through radio and touring acts. France pushed chanson into more modern pop, Germany experimented with avant-garde classical and electronic textures, Italy leaned into melodic pop and film soundtracks, while the Balkans fused folk rhythms with jazz and beat music. In Scandinavia, jazz scenes were especially strong (Sweden and Norway were early adopters of modern jazz).</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What you can find in this playlist -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">What you can find in this playlist            </h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-6">
            <!-- Subsections -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              <p>Chanson (France): Introspective, poetic French pop — </p>
              
              <div class="flex flex-col items-center my-2 space-x-2">
              <img src="https://syvkefpljdcoricvmqcy.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/images/europe_assets/content_images/edith_piaf.jpeg" alt="Edith Piaf" class="w-64 h-64 rounded-full object-cover">
              <span class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Edith Piaf</span> <br/>
              </div>
             Edith Piaf paved the way, while Jacques Brel and Serge Gainsbourg made it stylish and provocative.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <p>Yé-Yé (France): Youth-driven bubblegum pop — Françoise Hardy, France Gall; think stylish teen pop with a European twist. It was called so because the term "yé-yé" is a French adaptation of the English exclamation "yeah! yeah!"</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              <p>Schlager (Germany, Austria, Switzerland): Catchy, sentimental pop that dominated radio — kind of like Europe’s easy-listening.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <p>French & Italian composers (Italy): In Italy, composers like Armando Trovajoli scored the country’s wave of risqué comedies and soft-porn films, blending lounge jazz, bossa nova, and easy-listening orchestrations. These playful, seductive soundtracks often became more memorable than the films themselves, later rediscovered as cult classics by crate-diggers and DJs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
             <img src="https://syvkefpljdcoricvmqcy.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/images/europe_assets/content_images/Lesbo.jpeg" alt="Lesbo movie poster" class="w-64 h-auto">
             <img src="https://syvkefpljdcoricvmqcy.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/images/europe_assets/content_images/Porfumo.jpeg" alt="Perfumo Movie Poster" class="w-64 h-auto ">

            </div>
           

            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <p>Nueva Canción (Spain under Franco, also Latin-linked): Folk revival with subtle political undertones despite censorship.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              <p>Eastern Bloc Jazz & Beat Bands: Underground jazz in Poland and Czechoslovakia became major youth outlets. Rock groups (like Hungary’s Illés) pushed against state control. Some Soviet artists used to rename their songs and band names to skip censorship.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <p>Scandinavian Jazz: Jan Johansson and others mixed Nordic folk with jazz harmonies.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              <p>Russian Bard Songs: Acoustic, poetic, semi-subversive music passed hand to hand (e.g., Vladimir Vysotsky).</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- The Tech Factor -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9.75 17L9 20l-1 1h8l-1-1-.75-3M3 13h18M5 17h14a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Technological changes </h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <p>Instruments in transition:</p>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">  <p>
West Europe: Electric guitars (Fender, Gibson) became available, and German companies like Höfner (famous for Paul McCartney’s (From the Beatles) bass,
though UK, the brand itself is German) helped spread electric instruments locally. Italian companies like Eko became major guitar producers for European beat bands.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center my-2 space-x-2">
              <img src="https://syvkefpljdcoricvmqcy.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/images/europe_assets/content_images/Hofner.jpeg" alt="Paul McCartney playing a Hofner bass" class="w-64 h-64 rounded-xl object-cover">
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <p>Eastern Europe & USSR: Instruments were harder to access — many bands built their own amps, guitars, and drum kits. Accordion and mandolin were still staples in folk.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
                <p>Nordics & Germany: Early adoption of synthesizers and tape experiments tied to avant-garde classical traditions. Cologne’s electronic music studios (Stockhausen, etc.) influenced younger musicians.</p>
            </div>

            </div>  
            
          
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Notable Artists -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"></path>
            </svg>
              <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Notable Artists</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            {data.notable_artists.map((region, index) => (
              <div>
                <h5 class={`text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2  pb-2 ${index%2==0? 'border-[#FEE96A]' : 'border-[#C13870]'}`}>{region.title}</h5>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                  {region.artists.map((artist) => (
                    <div class={`${index%3==0? 'bg-[#FEE96A]/10' : 'bg-[#C13870]/10'} p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30`}>
                     
                      {artist.image && <img src={artist.image} alt={artist.name} class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover">}
                      <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">{artist.name}</h6>
                      <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">{artist.description}</p>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
              </div>
            
          
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


</div>

<script>
  // Accordion functionality
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const accordionTriggers = document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-trigger');
    
    accordionTriggers.forEach(trigger => {
      trigger.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const accordionItem = trigger.closest('.accordion-item');
        const content = accordionItem?.querySelector('.accordion-content');
        const icon = trigger.querySelector('.accordion-icon');
        
        if (content && icon) {
          const isOpen = !content.classList.contains('hidden');
          

          
          // Toggle current accordion
          if (isOpen) {
            content.classList.add('hidden');
            icon.classList.remove('rotate-180');
          } else {
            content.classList.remove('hidden');
            icon.classList.add('rotate-180');
          }
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>


